MXOLISI MNGADI  A 38-YEAR-OLD man, suspected of killing a Mandeni chief in 2016, remains in custody following his court appearance on Monday, the Hawks said. He briefly appeared at the Eshowe Magistrate's Court, where he heard he will remain in custody until Monday, January 22, said KwaZulu-Natal Hawks spokesperson Captain Simphiwe Mhlongo. He faced charges of murder and attempted murder. Mhlongo said the suspect's name could not be released yet. “We are waiting for the identification parade, then we can release it,” he said. Chief Linda Mathonsi (58) was shot in the head and neck on the evening of December 5, 2016, around 6pm, while travelling with his daughter (25), who was also shot on the arm. They had been travelling in the Chappies area of Sundumbili in Mandeni when a car drove up alongside their car and an occupant began firing at them.      24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  